                <h1>What to Do If Your Background Check Contains Errors</h1>
                <p>If your background check is incorrect, promptly gather supporting documents to dispute the findings. Contact the background check company to request corrections and file a dispute. Stay organized and keep records of all communications. As a precaution, check your own background regularly to prevent future issues.</p>
